A leader of the Odua People Congress (OPC) in Akure Temitope Alo aka Ashamo has been remanded in a Correctional centre for allegedly disrupting religious worship at the Akure Central Mosque. Alo and his gang reportedly flogged one Akeem Aminu and inflicted bodily injuries on him with a cutlass. He was arraigned on five-count charges bordering on assault and conduct capable of causing a breach of public peace. Police Prosecutor, Inspector Abdulateef Suliaman, said the defendant and others at large committed the offence around 2:30 pm on March 13, 2022, at Central Mosque Oja-Oba in Akure. Suliaman said the victim, the mosque traffic controller, sustained serious injury and was in critical condition at the police clinic.   Lawyer’s absence stalls Sowore’s arraignment on cybercrime…     Six in police net for allegedly parading widow naked in…     I’ve no hand over insecurity in Katsina, says SSG   He stated that the disorderly manner caused a breach of peace in the town and made the worshippers run helter-skelter for their dear lives. According to him, the offence contravenes Sections 519,252,351,249(d), 205(2), and 206 of the Criminal Code, Cap 37, Vol. 1, Laws of Ondo State, 2016. The defendant pleaded not guilty to the charges preferred against him while his lawyer, Femi Adetoye, applied for his bail, promising that he would not jump bail. Presiding Magistrate, N.K Aladejana, ordered the remand of the defendant at the Correctional Centre, and adjourned the case to March 24, 2020, for hearing.